trans-unit.source: Contains methods, properties, and events to support navigation.
trans-unit.target: Contém métodos, propriedades e os eventos para suportar a navegação.

trans-unit.source: NavigationService encapsulates the ability to download content within the context of a browser-style navigation.
trans-unit.target: NavigationService encapsula a capacidade de transferir o conteúdo no contexto de uma navegação do browser estilo.

trans-unit.source: Content can be any type of [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_winfx](~/add/includes/tla2sharptla-winfx-md.md)] object and [!INCLUDE[TLA#tla_html](~/add/includes/tlasharptla-html-md.md)] files.
trans-unit.target: O conteúdo pode ser qualquer tipo de [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_winfx](~/add/includes/tla2sharptla-winfx-md.md)] objeto e [!INCLUDE[TLA#tla_html](~/add/includes/tlasharptla-html-md.md)] ficheiros.

trans-unit.source: In general, however, pages are the preferred as the way to package content for navigation (see <xref:System.Windows.Controls.Page>).
trans-unit.target: Em geral, no entanto, as páginas são preferenciais como a forma de conteúdo do pacote para navegação (consulte <xref:System.Windows.Controls.Page>).</xref:System.Windows.Controls.Page>

trans-unit.source: Content can be navigated to by providing an instance of an object and calling an overload of the <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService.Navigate%2A> method that accepts an object: - <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService.Navigate%28System.Object%29?displayProperty=fullName> - <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService.Navigate%28System.Object%2CSystem.Object%29?displayProperty=fullName> Alternatively, content can be navigated to by passing a relative or absolute [!INCLUDE[TLA#tla_uri](~/add/includes/tlasharptla-uri-md.md)] to one of the <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService.Navigate%2A> method overloads that accepts a [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_uri](~/add/includes/tla2sharptla-uri-md.md)]: - <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService.Navigate%28System.Uri%29?displayProperty=fullName> - <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService.Navigate%28System.Uri%2CSystem.Object%29?displayProperty=fullName> - <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService.Navigate%28System.Uri%2CSystem.Object%2CSystem.Boolean%29?displayProperty=fullName> When content is navigated to by [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_uri](~/add/includes/tla2sharptla-uri-md.md)], NavigationService will return an object that contains the content.
trans-unit.target: Conteúdo pode navegar para fornecer uma instância de um objeto e chamar uma sobrecarga do <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService.Navigate%2A>método que aceite um objecto:- <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService.Navigate%28System.Object%29?displayProperty=fullName>- <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService.Navigate%28System.Object%2CSystem.Object%29?displayProperty=fullName>em alternativa, o conteúdo pode ser direcionado ao transmitir um caminho relativo ou absoluto [!INCLUDE[TLA#tla_uri](~/add/includes/tlasharptla-uri-md.md)] do <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService.Navigate%2A>sobrecargas do método que aceita um [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_uri](~/add/includes/tla2sharptla-uri-md.md)]:- <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService.Navigate%28System.Uri%29?displayProperty=fullName>- <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService.Navigate%28System.Uri%2CSystem.Object%29?displayProperty=fullName>- <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService.Navigate%28System.Uri%2CSystem.Object%2CSystem.Boolean%29?displayProperty=fullName>quando o conteúdo é direcionado para por [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_uri](~/add/includes/tla2sharptla-uri-md.md)], NavigationService irá devolver um objeto que contém o conteúdo.</xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService.Navigate%28System.Uri%2CSystem.Object%2CSystem.Boolean%29?displayProperty=fullName> </xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService.Navigate%28System.Uri%2CSystem.Object%29?displayProperty=fullName> </xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService.Navigate%28System.Uri%29?displayProperty=fullName> </xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService.Navigate%2A> </xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService.Navigate%28System.Object%2CSystem.Object%29?displayProperty=fullName> </xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService.Navigate%28System.Object%29?displayProperty=fullName> </xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService.Navigate%2A>

trans-unit.source: The lifetime of a navigation can be tracked through the following events: - <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService.Navigating> - <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService.Navigated> - <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService.NavigationProgress> - <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService.NavigationFailed> - <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService.NavigationStopped> - <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService.LoadCompleted> - <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService.FragmentNavigation>.
trans-unit.target: A duração de uma navegação pode ser controlada através os seguintes eventos:- <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService.Navigating>- <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService.Navigated>- <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService.NavigationProgress>- <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService.NavigationFailed>- <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService.NavigationStopped>- <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService.LoadCompleted>- <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService.FragmentNavigation>.</xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService.FragmentNavigation> </xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService.LoadCompleted> </xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService.NavigationStopped> </xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService.NavigationFailed> </xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService.NavigationProgress> </xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService.Navigated> </xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService.Navigating>

trans-unit.source: Not all events are raised each time that a navigation occurs; the set of events that are raised is determined by the type of navigation that occurs (content or content fragment) and how the navigation completes (canceled, stopped, or failed).
trans-unit.target: Nem todos os eventos são gerados sempre que ocorre uma navegação; o conjunto de eventos que são gerados é determinado pelo tipo de navegação que ocorre (fragmento de conteúdo ou conteúdo) e como conclui o painel de navegação (cancelada, parado ou falha).

trans-unit.source: The following figure illustrates the sequence in which these events are raised: ![Page navigation flow chart](~/add/media/navigationoverviewfigure11.png "Page navigation flow chart") During or after a navigation, NavigationService provides information about the content that is being navigated to, including the [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_uri](~/add/includes/tla2sharptla-uri-md.md)] of the content being navigated to (<xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService.Source%2A>), the [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_uri](~/add/includes/tla2sharptla-uri-md.md)] of the current content (<xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService.CurrentSource%2A>), and an object that contains the content that was navigated to (<xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService.Content%2A>).
trans-unit.target: A figura seguinte ilustra a sequência em que estes eventos são gerados: ![página navegação fluxograma](~/add/media/navigationoverviewfigure11.png "página navegação fluxograma") durante ou após uma navegação NavigationService fornece informações sobre o conteúdo que está a ser utilizado, incluindo o [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_uri](~/add/includes/tla2sharptla-uri-md.md)] do conteúdo que está a ser utilizado (<xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService.Source%2A>), o [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_uri](~/add/includes/tla2sharptla-uri-md.md)] do conteúdo atual (<xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService.CurrentSource%2A>) e um objeto que contém o conteúdo que foi utilizado (<xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService.Content%2A>).</xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService.Content%2A> </xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService.CurrentSource%2A> </xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService.Source%2A>

trans-unit.source: When content is navigated to, NavigationService records the navigation as an entry in navigation history.
trans-unit.target: Quando o conteúdo é direcionado para, NavigationService regista a navegação como uma entrada no histórico de navegação.

trans-unit.source: An entry is added to back navigation history when either a new navigation occurs, by calling the <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService.Navigate%2A> method, or by navigating to an entry in forward navigation history, by calling <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService.GoForward%2A>.
trans-unit.target: Uma entrada é adicionada ao fazer uma cópia de histórico de navegação quando ocorre a uma navegação novo, chamando o <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService.Navigate%2A>método, ou ao navegar para uma entrada no histórico de navegação de avanço, chamando <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService.GoForward%2A>.</xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService.GoForward%2A> </xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService.Navigate%2A>

trans-unit.source: An entry is added to forward navigation history by navigating to an entry in back navigation history, by calling <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService.GoBack%2A>.
trans-unit.target: Uma entrada é adicionada ao histórico de navegação de avanço, navegando até uma entrada anterior no histórico de navegação, chamando <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService.GoBack%2A>.</xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService.GoBack%2A>

trans-unit.source: <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService.CanGoBack%2A> and <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService.CanGoForward%2A> report whether there are entries in back and forward navigation history, respectively.
trans-unit.target: <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService.CanGoBack%2A>e <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService.CanGoForward%2A>reportar se existem entradas em volta e o histórico de navegação de avanço, respetivamente.</xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService.CanGoForward%2A></xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService.CanGoBack%2A>

trans-unit.source: Also, the most recent entry in back navigation history can be removed by calling <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService.RemoveBackEntry%2A>.
trans-unit.target: Além disso, a entrada mais recente no histórico de navegação de back-pode ser removida ao chamar <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService.RemoveBackEntry%2A>.</xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService.RemoveBackEntry%2A>

trans-unit.source: By default, NavigationService does not store an instance of a content object in navigation history.
trans-unit.target: Por predefinição, NavigationService não armazena uma instância de um objeto do conteúdo no histórico de navegação.

trans-unit.source: Instead, NavigationService creates a new instance of the content object each time it is navigated to by using navigation history.
trans-unit.target: Em vez disso, NavigationService cria uma nova instância do objeto do conteúdo sempre que é utilizado com o histórico de navegação.

trans-unit.source: This behavior is designed to avoid excessive memory consumption when large numbers and large pieces of content are being navigated to.
trans-unit.target: Este comportamento é concebido para evitar o consumo de memória excessiva quando grandes quantidades e grande peças de conteúdo estão a ser utilizadas.

trans-unit.source: Consequently, the state of the content is not remembered from one navigation to the next.
trans-unit.target: Por conseguinte, o estado do conteúdo não é memorizado de navegação de um para a seguinte.

trans-unit.source: However, [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_wpf](~/add/includes/ajax-current-ext-md.md)] provides several techniques by which you can store a piece of state for a piece of content in navigation history.
trans-unit.target: No entanto, [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_wpf](~/add/includes/ajax-current-ext-md.md)] fornece várias técnicas através do qual pode armazenar um fragmento do Estado de uma peça de conteúdo no histórico de navegação.

trans-unit.source: Using <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService.AddBackEntry%2A>, you can also remember multiple sets of state for a single page instance.
trans-unit.target: Utilizar <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService.AddBackEntry%2A>, também pode memorizar vários conjuntos de estado para uma instância de página única.</xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService.AddBackEntry%2A>

trans-unit.source: NavigationService is `sealed` class and, therefore, cannot be instantiated; instead, NavigationService is used by navigators to enable navigation.
trans-unit.target: É NavigationService `sealed` classe e, por conseguinte, não é possível instanciar; em vez disso, NavigationService é utilizada pelo navegadores para permitir a navegação.

trans-unit.source: In [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_wpf](~/add/includes/ajax-current-ext-md.md)], there are two navigators: <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationWindow>, <xref:System.Windows.Controls.Frame>.
trans-unit.target: No [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_wpf](~/add/includes/ajax-current-ext-md.md)], existem dois navegadores: <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationWindow>, <xref:System.Windows.Controls.Frame>.</xref:System.Windows.Controls.Frame> </xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationWindow>

trans-unit.source: Visually, [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_xbap#plural](~/add/includes/tla2sharptla-xbapsharpplural-md.md)] use [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_ie7](~/add/includes/tla2sharptla-ie7-md.md)] as a navigator, to provide an integrated user experience.
trans-unit.target: Visualmente, [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_xbap#plural](~/add/includes/tla2sharptla-xbapsharpplural-md.md)] utilizar [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_ie7](~/add/includes/tla2sharptla-ie7-md.md)] como um navegador, para proporcionar uma experiência de utilizador integrado.

trans-unit.source: Physically, however, [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_xbap#plural](~/add/includes/tla2sharptla-xbapsharpplural-md.md)] actually use <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationWindow> as the navigator; the <xref:System.Windows.Application.MainWindow%2A> property of an [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_xbap](~/add/includes/ajax-current-ext-md.md)] running in [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_ie7](~/add/includes/tla2sharptla-ie7-md.md)] will return a reference to the <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationWindow>, and the navigation history that is managed by the <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationWindow> is integrated with the navigation history that is managed by [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_ie7](~/add/includes/tla2sharptla-ie7-md.md)] in the following ways: - When content is navigated to by calling <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService.Navigate%2A>, <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService.GoBack%2A>, and <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService.GoForward%2A> from within an [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_xbap](~/add/includes/ajax-current-ext-md.md)] the relevant navigation history entries are also added to [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_ie7](~/add/includes/tla2sharptla-ie7-md.md)] navigation history.
trans-unit.target: Fisicamente, no entanto, [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_xbap#plural](~/add/includes/tla2sharptla-xbapsharpplural-md.md)] realmente utiliza <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationWindow>como navegador; o <xref:System.Windows.Application.MainWindow%2A>propriedade de uma [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_xbap](~/add/includes/ajax-current-ext-md.md)] em execução no [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_ie7](~/add/includes/tla2sharptla-ie7-md.md)] irá devolver uma referência para o <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationWindow>e o histórico de navegação que é gerido pelo <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationWindow>está integrado com o histórico de navegação que é gerido pelo [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_ie7](~/add/includes/tla2sharptla-ie7-md.md)] das seguintes formas: - quando o conteúdo é direcionado para chamando <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService.Navigate%2A>, <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService.GoBack%2A>, e <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService.GoForward%2A>a partir de uma [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_xbap](~/add/includes/ajax-current-ext-md.md)] as entradas do histórico de navegação relevantes também são adicionadas à [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_ie7](~/add/includes/tla2sharptla-ie7-md.md)] histórico de navegação.</xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService.GoForward%2A> </xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService.GoBack%2A> </xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService.Navigate%2A> </xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationWindow> </xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationWindow> </xref:System.Windows.Application.MainWindow%2A> </xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationWindow>

trans-unit.source: - When entries in the [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_ie7](~/add/includes/tla2sharptla-ie7-md.md)] navigation [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_ui](~/add/includes/ajax-current-ext-md.md)] are selected, [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_ie7](~/add/includes/tla2sharptla-ie7-md.md)] causes NavigationService to navigate back or forwards to the content that is associated with those entries.

trans-unit.source: If <xref:System.Windows.Controls.Frame> provides its own navigation history, it can display its own navigation [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_ui](~/add/includes/ajax-current-ext-md.md)] to navigate through the entries in navigation history; those entries are not added to the navigation history of the host navigator (<xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationWindow>, <xref:System.Windows.Controls.Frame>, [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_iegeneric](~/add/includes/tla2sharptla-iegeneric-md.md)]) and, consequently, cannot be navigated to from the navigation [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_ui](~/add/includes/ajax-current-ext-md.md)] of each (see <xref:System.Windows.Controls.Frame.JournalOwnership%2A>).
trans-unit.target: Se <xref:System.Windows.Controls.Frame>fornece o suas próprias histórico de navegação, pode apresentar a seus próprios navegação [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_ui](~/add/includes/ajax-current-ext-md.md)] de navegar pelas entradas no histórico de navegação; essas entradas não são adicionadas ao histórico de navegação do navegador de anfitrião (<xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationWindow>, <xref:System.Windows.Controls.Frame>, [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_iegeneric](~/add/includes/tla2sharptla-iegeneric-md.md)]) e, consequentemente, não é possível navegar a partir do painel de navegação [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_ui](~/add/includes/ajax-current-ext-md.md)] de cada (consulte <xref:System.Windows.Controls.Frame.JournalOwnership%2A>).</xref:System.Windows.Controls.Frame.JournalOwnership%2A> </xref:System.Windows.Controls.Frame> </xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationWindow> </xref:System.Windows.Controls.Frame>

trans-unit.source: Since navigations are asynchronous, it is possible for multiple navigations to be in progress at the same time.
trans-unit.target: Uma vez que navigations são assíncronas, é possível que vários navigations estar em curso, ao mesmo tempo.

trans-unit.source: For example, if there are two child frames on a single page, both frames could be navigating.
trans-unit.target: Por exemplo, se existirem dois frames Jumbo subordinados numa única página, podem navegar ambos os fotogramas.

trans-unit.source: In this case, the various navigation events that are raised by <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService> may be raised multiple times, one for each piece of content that is being navigated to, and not necessarily in order that the navigations were requested.
trans-unit.target: Neste caso, os vários eventos de navegação que são gerados por <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService>pode ser gerada várias vezes, um de cada peça de conteúdo que está a ser utilizado e não necessariamente que o navigations foram pedidas.</xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService>

trans-unit.source: Consequently, if a particular navigation request needs to process data that is specific to the individual request, it cannot use data that is available to all navigation requests.
trans-unit.target: Por conseguinte, se um pedido de navegação específico necessita de processar dados específicos para o pedido individual, não é possível utilizar os dados que está disponíveis para todos os pedidos de navegação.

trans-unit.source: Instead, you can use `navigationState` to pass data for navigation processing that is specific to one navigation request.
trans-unit.target: Em vez disso, pode utilizar `navigationState` para transmitir dados para navegação processamento que é específica ao pedido de uma navegação.

trans-unit.target: Se cancelar a navegação, outros eventos de navegação não são gerados.

trans-unit.target: > [!NOTE] > Se a aplicação será alojada no browser, não é possível impedir que o utilizador de navegar para fora da sua aplicação por cancelar o eventos Navigating.

trans-unit.source: After the first piece of content is navigated to by a navigator (<xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationWindow>, <xref:System.Windows.Controls.Frame>), each piece of content that is navigated away from is added to navigation history.

trans-unit.target: NavigationFailed foi transmitido um <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationFailedEventArgs>que contém informações sobre a exceção e os detalhes do painel de navegação que causou a exceção.</xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationFailedEventArgs>

trans-unit.source: Occurs periodically during a download to provide navigation progress information.
trans-unit.target: Ocorre periodicamente durante uma transferência para fornecer informações de progresso de navegação.

trans-unit.source: NavigationProgress is passed a <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationProgressEventArgs> which exposes the following progress information: - Number of bytes downloaded so far (<xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationProgressEventArgs.BytesRead%2A>).
trans-unit.target: NavigationProgress foi transmitido um <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationProgressEventArgs>que expõe as seguintes informações de progresso:-número de bytes transferidos até ao momento (<xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationProgressEventArgs.BytesRead%2A>).</xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationProgressEventArgs.BytesRead%2A> </xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationProgressEventArgs>

trans-unit.source: - Number of total bytes to download (<xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationProgressEventArgs.MaxBytes%2A>).
trans-unit.target: -Número total de bytes para transferir (<xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationProgressEventArgs.MaxBytes%2A>).</xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationProgressEventArgs.MaxBytes%2A>

trans-unit.source: NavigationProgress is raised once for every 1024 bytes of content downloaded, and once more if the number of remaining bytes is ever less than 1024 bytes.
trans-unit.target: NavigationProgress é desencadeado depois de cada 1024 bytes do conteúdo transferido e mais uma vez, se o número de bytes restantes é alguma vez inferior a 1024 bytes.

trans-unit.source: For this reason, handling NavigationProgress provides a useful way to track and display the progress of a current download.
trans-unit.target: Por este motivo, o processamento NavigationProgress fornece uma forma útil para controlar e apresentar o progresso de uma transferência atual.

trans-unit.source: NavigationProgress won't be raised in some cases, such as when the same piece of content is navigated to, or when a content fragment is navigated to on content that is currently loaded (that is, the value of the <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService.Content%2A> property).
trans-unit.target: Não será desencadeado NavigationProgress em alguns casos, tal como quando a mesma peça do conteúdo é direcionada para ou quando um fragmento de conteúdo é utilizado no conteúdo que está actualmente carregado (ou seja, o valor da <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService.Content%2A>propriedade).</xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService.Content%2A>

trans-unit.source: When navigating to a compiled XAML resource, the final NavigationProgress event may not be raised.
trans-unit.target: Quando navegar para um recurso XAML compilado, o evento de NavigationProgress final não pode ser gerado.

trans-unit.source: This means that at the end of the download, the last reported <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationProgressEventArgs.BytesRead%2A> value may not equal the <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationProgressEventArgs.MaxBytes%2A> value.
trans-unit.target: Isto significa que no final da transferência, o último reportados <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationProgressEventArgs.BytesRead%2A>valor não pode ser igual a <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationProgressEventArgs.MaxBytes%2A>valor.</xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationProgressEventArgs.MaxBytes%2A> </xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationProgressEventArgs.BytesRead%2A>

trans-unit.source: The most recent <xref href="System.Windows.Navigation.JournalEntry"></xref> in back navigation history, if there is one.
trans-unit.target: O mais recente <xref href="System.Windows.Navigation.JournalEntry"> </xref> no histórico de navegação anterior, se existir um.

trans-unit.source: Gets or sets the [!INCLUDE[TLA#tla_uri](~/add/includes/tlasharptla-uri-md.md)] of the current content, or the [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_uri](~/add/includes/tla2sharptla-uri-md.md)] of new content that is currently being navigated to.
trans-unit.target: Obtém ou define o [!INCLUDE[TLA#tla_uri](~/add/includes/tlasharptla-uri-md.md)] do conteúdo atual, ou o [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_uri](~/add/includes/tla2sharptla-uri-md.md)] de conteúdo novo que está atualmente a ser utilizado.

trans-unit.source: If you set this property to a different [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_uri](~/add/includes/tla2sharptla-uri-md.md)] than the one currently being displayed, the navigator (<xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationWindow>, <xref:System.Windows.Controls.Frame>) navigates to the specified [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_uri](~/add/includes/tla2sharptla-uri-md.md)].
trans-unit.target: Se definir esta propriedade para outro [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_uri](~/add/includes/tla2sharptla-uri-md.md)] daquela atualmente a ser apresentado, navegador (<xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationWindow>, <xref:System.Windows.Controls.Frame>) navega para especificado [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_uri](~/add/includes/tla2sharptla-uri-md.md)].</xref:System.Windows.Controls.Frame> </xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationWindow>

trans-unit.source: Source is set to the content that is loaded from the [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_uri](~/add/includes/tla2sharptla-uri-md.md)] that is navigated to, unless the navigation is canceled.
trans-unit.target: A origem está definida para o conteúdo que é carregado a partir de [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_uri](~/add/includes/tla2sharptla-uri-md.md)] que é utilizado, a menos que a navegação foi cancelada.

trans-unit.source: Source can be set with a fragment-only [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_uri](~/add/includes/tla2sharptla-uri-md.md)], and can be set to `null`.
trans-unit.target: Origem pode ser definida com um fragmento só [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_uri](~/add/includes/tla2sharptla-uri-md.md)]e pode ser definido como `null`.

trans-unit.source: A <xref:System.Uri> that contains the [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_uri](~/add/includes/tla2sharptla-uri-md.md)] for the current content, or the content that is currently being navigated to.
trans-unit.target: A <xref:System.Uri>que contém o [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_uri](~/add/includes/tla2sharptla-uri-md.md)] para o conteúdo atual ou o conteúdo que está atualmente a ser utilizado.</xref:System.Uri>

trans-unit.source: Stops further downloading of content for the current navigation request.
trans-unit.target: Interrompe ainda mais a transferir conteúdo para o pedido atual de navegação.

trans-unit.source: StopLoading can be called as soon as <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService.Navigate%2A> returns, and stops navigation that is in progress in child frames.
trans-unit.target: Pode ser chamado StopLoading assim <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService.Navigate%2A>devolve e deixa de navegação que está em curso no frames Jumbo subordinados.</xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService.Navigate%2A>

trans-unit.source: (<xref:System.Windows.Controls.Frame>).
trans-unit.target: (<xref:System.Windows.Controls.Frame>).</xref:System.Windows.Controls.Frame>

trans-unit.source: Calling the StopLoading method raises the <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService.NavigationStopped> event.
trans-unit.target: Chamar o método StopLoading gera o <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService.NavigationStopped>eventos.</xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationService.NavigationStopped>

trans-unit.source: > [!NOTE] > StopLoading must be called on the same thread that initiated the navigation.
trans-unit.target: > [!NOTE] > StopLoading tem de ser chamado no mesmo thread que iniciou o painel de navegação.
